Bebeto, Couto to grace event  The Flying Eagles of Nigeria have been placed on Pot 2 for the 2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup draw which takes place on February 24. FIFA, in a release, ahead of the event which would hold in Gdynia, Poland, listed newly-crowned African champions Mali, New Zealand, Colombia, Korea Republic and Italy alongside the Flying Eagles on Pot 2. The seeding was based on ranking built on past performances of the 24 teams that will feature in the tournament. Poland, Portugal, Uruguay, France, USA and Mexico are in Pot 1 while Saudi Arabia, Senegal, Argentina, Ecuador, Ukraine, Honduras are in Pot 3 with Pot 4 having Japan, South Africa, Panama, Norway, Qatar, Tahiti. Hosts Poland will be pre-assigned to position A1 and play all their group matches in Lodz Meanwhile, FIFA Legends Bebeto and Fernando Couto will decide the fate of the 24 FIFA U-20 World Cup 2019 contenders as they join the stage for the Official Draw in Gdynia, Poland, on 24 February. Bebeto, a winner of the FIFA World Cupâ„¢ in 1994 and the FIFA U-20 World Cup 1983, and Couto, who won the FIFA U-20 World Cup in 1989, will be the draw assistants for the ceremony at the Gdynia Arena. The tournament will hold from May 29 to June 16 in six Polish cities namely Bielsko-Biala, Bydgoszcz, Gdynia, Lodz, Lublin and Tychy.